This dataset contains 1,000 records with 10 numerical feature columns and one target column named TARGET CLASS. 
The features are artificially generated and represent normalized values used for classification tasks. 
The target column has two balanced classes, 0 and 1, making it suitable for supervised machine learning models such as K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN). 
Since all input variables are numeric and on different scales, feature standardization is recommended before training. 
  The dataset is ideal for practicing data preprocessing, visualization, model training, evaluation, and hyperparameter tuning techniques in Python.
